@startuml
title Morning Briefing Backend Package Diagram
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam linetype ortho
left to right direction

package "Web UI\n(AngularJS SPA)" as WebUi

package "Backend API\nNode.js + Fastify" as Api {
  package "API Layer" as ApiLayer {
    [Routes]
    [Schemas]
    [Controllers]
  }

  package "Application Layer" as AppLayer {
    [Dashboard Use Cases]
    [Widget Use Cases]
    [Connector Use Cases]
    [Admin Configuration Use Cases]
    [Briefing Use Cases]
    [Audio Briefing Use Cases]
  }

  package "Domain Layer" as DomainLayer {
    [Dashboard Domain]
    [Widget Domain]
    [Connector Domain]
    [Snapshot Domain]
  }

  package "Infrastructure Layer" as InfraLayer {
    [Postgres Repositories]
    [Connector Clients]
    [Secret Store]
    [Snapshot Queue Publisher]
    [Snapshot Job Processor]
    [Tenant AI Configuration]
    [LLM Provider]
    [TTS Provider]
    [Audio Storage]
    [Observability]
  }
}

database "PostgreSQL\n(Local + AWS RDS)" as Postgres
queue "Amazon SQS\nSnapshot Jobs + DLQ" as Sqs
cloud "AWS Lambda\nSnapshot Worker" as Lambda
cloud "EventBridge Scheduler\nWidget Snapshot Refresh" as SnapshotScheduler
cloud "EventBridge Scheduler\nDashboard Audio Refresh" as AudioScheduler
cloud "Secret Backend\n(Local env / AWS Secrets Manager)" as Secrets
cloud "External Providers\nWeather / Calendar / Email / Tasks / News" as Providers
cloud "OpenAI Responses API" as OpenAiResponses
cloud "AWS Polly" as AwsPolly

WebUi --> ApiLayer : REST /api/v1
ApiLayer --> AppLayer
AppLayer --> DomainLayer
AppLayer --> InfraLayer
InfraLayer --> Postgres
InfraLayer --> Sqs
InfraLayer --> Secrets
InfraLayer --> Providers
InfraLayer --> OpenAiResponses
InfraLayer --> AwsPolly
SnapshotScheduler --> AppLayer : invokes widget snapshot enqueue
AudioScheduler --> AppLayer : invokes dashboard audio enqueue
Sqs --> Lambda : event source mapping
Lambda --> [Snapshot Job Processor]
[Snapshot Queue Publisher] ..> Sqs : enqueue widget commands
[Audio Briefing Use Cases] ..> Sqs : enqueue audio commands
[Snapshot Job Processor] ..> [Briefing Use Cases] : generate widget snapshots
[Snapshot Job Processor] ..> [Audio Briefing Use Cases] : generate dashboard audio
[Snapshot Job Processor] ..> Postgres : job state + snapshots
[Admin Configuration Use Cases] ..> [Tenant AI Configuration] : load/update shared model + key
[Audio Briefing Use Cases] ..> [LLM Provider] : script generation
[Audio Briefing Use Cases] ..> [TTS Provider] : audio generation
[Audio Briefing Use Cases] ..> [Audio Storage] : persist files
[Audio Briefing Use Cases] ..> Postgres : metadata + preferences
[LLM Provider] ..> [Tenant AI Configuration]
[LLM Provider] ..> OpenAiResponses
[TTS Provider] ..> AwsPolly

[Connector Clients] ..> [Connector Domain]
[Postgres Repositories] ..> [Dashboard Domain]
[Postgres Repositories] ..> [Widget Domain]
[Postgres Repositories] ..> [Snapshot Domain]

note bottom of WebUi
UI communicates with backend only through REST.
No direct database or provider access.
end note

note bottom of InfraLayer
The worker logic stays inside the modular monolith,
while ECS scheduled tasks trigger the daily UTC refresh jobs
and SQS provides the queue runtime for async processing.
Dashboard and widget rows also carry is_generating flags
so admin views can reflect in-flight regeneration state.
end note

@enduml
